*Iterating over a string is useful when trying to get the length of a string or reading a string and
building another.
  Basic Template:
  int x = Word.length();
  char y = word.charAt(x - 1); <-- need "- 1" to avoid outofboundsexception error
  
  ex: Reversing a string
  public static reverse(String s){
  String r = "";
  for (int i = s.length() - 1; i >=0; i--){
  r =+ s.charAt(i);
  }
  return r;
  }
  
*You can also use indexOf() to search for a specific char of a string
  ex: String fruit = "banana";
      int index = fruit.indexOf('a'); <-- this returns 1

*Accessing substrings
  ex: String fruit = "banana";
  fruit.substring(0,3); <-- returns banana
  NOTE: if only one argument is provided for substring method, then it will return the corresponding
        point in index and then the rest of the string.
      
